<ul id="parentul">
    <li id="first">first Child</li>
    <li>Hello World!</li>
    <li id="web"></li>
    <li>bye!</li>
</ul>

var parent = document.getElementById("parentul");
var web = document.getElementById("web");

DOM ( Read Only)
childElementCount parent.childElementCount // 4
firstElementChild parent.firstElementChild //<li id="first" ..</li>
lastElementChild parent.lastElementChild //<li>bye!</li>
nextElementSibling web.nextElementSibling //<li>bye!</li>
parentElement web.parentElement //<ul id="parentul" ...
previousElementSibling web.previousElementSibling //<li>Hello World!</li>

children parent.children //[li, li, li, li] (Read Only)

<form action="/submits" id="login">
    <input type="text" id="id"/>
    <input type="password" id="pw"/>
    <input type="submit" value="" id="submit" />
</form>

var loginForm = document.getElementById("login");
var txtId = document.getElementById("id");
var txtPw = document.getElementById("pw");
var btnSubmit = document.getElementById("submit");
var br = document.createElement("br"); // br  
function method () {
    console.log("clicked!");
}
addEventListener() txtId.addEventListener('click', method) click method
appendChild() loginForm.appendChild(br) br .
click() btnSubmit.click() .
focus() txtId.focus() .
setAttribute() btnSubmit.setAttribute("value","")
insertBefore() . loginForm.insertBefore(br, txtId) id .
querySelector() css loginForm.querySelector("input[type=password]") txtPw .
removeChild() loginForm.removeChild(btnSubmit) .
removeEventListener() txtId.removeEventListener('click', method) click .
